          "method": "POST",
          "postData": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"extract\",\"description\":\"A function available to call.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"success\":{\"type\":\"boolean\",\"description\":\"Was the question answered successfully? Does it include enough context to write great marketing copy for the business?\"},\"reasoning\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"Explain using the criteria why the question was or was not answered successfully.\"}},\"required\":[\"success\",\"reasoning\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"tool_choice\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"name\":\"extract\"},\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"\\n        # QA Evaluation Criteria\\n\\nALL answers must meet ALL four:\\n\\n1. **Specific** - Not vague (could describe 1000 businesses = fail)\\n2. **Actionable** - Can write marketing copy directly from it\\n3. **Authentic** - Their words, not marketing jargon (\\\"leverage synergies\\\" = fail)\\n4. **Insightful** - Shows understanding of business/audience\\n\\nClose but missing one element = NOT GREAT yet. Be critical but fair.\\n\\nOutput JSON: `{ success: boolean, reasoning: string }`\\n\\n        \\n        # QA: Solution\\n\\nNeed: Mechanism + transformation + differentiator + deliverable\\n\\n**Hormozi Value Equation** - Score mentally:\\n- Dream Outcome: Specific & quantified? (not \\\"more productive\\\")\\n- Perceived Likelihood: WHY it works? (method, track record)\\n- Time Delay: Timeline mentioned?\\n- Effort & Sacrifice: Level of work clear?\\n\\n**If 3+ score <7 → fail**\\n\\n**Unique Mechanism**: Named process = strong (\\\"4-Phase System\\\" not \\\"our approach\\\")\\n\\n**Reject**:\\n- Feature dumps without benefits\\n- \\\"Better/faster/cheaper\\\" (weak differentiation)\\n- Vague \\\"I help X do Y\\\"\\n- Unclear done-for-you vs DIY\\n\\n        \\n        <current_topic>solution</current_topic>\\n        \\n        <user_answer>Friend of the Pod has over 100+ filters to find the perfect guest for your show.\\n                We use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\n                We also use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\n                But what sets us apart is that we've trained proprietary models on messages that \\n                successful podcast hosts receive. We use this data to filter out pitches that \\n                are predicted to not be a good fit for your show.\\n            </user_answer>\\n        \\n        <existing_memory>No answer yet</existing_memory>\\n        \\n        <task>\\n        Evaluate if their answer is GREAT based on the criteria above.\\n        Output JSON: { \\\"success\\\": boolean, \\\"reasoning\\\": string }\\n        </task>\\n    \"}]}"
          },
          "queryString": [],
          "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages"
        },
        "response": {
          "bodySize": 2167,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 2167,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01LQKu2aBKVXN9cYcNS2LVpK\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01MMxWAhU3oV3Lc2ouWyiESW\",\"name\":\"extract\",\"input\":{\"success\":false,\"reasoning\":\"The answer fails on multiple critical criteria:\\n\\n**Specific (FAIL)**: \\\"100+ filters\\\" and \\\"match hosts and guests based on content, audience, and goals\\\" is vague—could describe dozens of podcast platforms. No concrete specifics about what makes the matching work or what results users get.\\n\\n**Actionable (PARTIAL)**: While there's a tangible feature (AI matching + proprietary models), there's no clear deliverable outcome. What does the user actually DO? Do they get a list? Do they book guests? Timeline unclear.\\n\\n**Authentic (FAIL)**: Heavy marketing jargon (\\\"proprietary models,\\\" \\\"trained on data,\\\" \\\"filter out pitches\\\") without explaining in real terms. Sounds like a pitch deck, not genuine insight into how it works.\\n\\n**Insightful (FAIL)**: Missing the Hormozi Value Equation entirely:\\n- Dream Outcome: Vague (\\\"perfect guest\\\") - not quantified (e.g., \\\"book 3 qualified guests/week\\\")\\n- Perceived Likelihood: WHY does AI matching work? No proof, track record, or method explanation beyond \\\"we trained models\\\"\\n- Time Delay: Zero mention of timeline\\n- Effort & Sacrifice: Unclear if this is done-for-you or DIY, how much work the host does\\n\\n**Additional Issues**:\\n- Repetition (same sentence twice) suggests lack of polish\\n- \\\"Sets us apart\\\" claim (proprietary models) is unverifiable and feels like feature-dumping\\n- No transformation shown—what changes for the podcast host's business?\\n- Reads like a feature list, not a solution to a real problem\\n\\n**What's missing**: Specific outcome (e.g., \\\"book 5 qualified guests/month in 30 minutes\\\"), why it works (track record or mechanism), and what the host actually experiences.\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1246,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":457,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
