          "headersSize": 573,
          "httpVersion": "HTTP/1.1",
          "method": "POST",
          "postData": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"extract\",\"description\":\"A function available to call.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"success\":{\"type\":\"boolean\",\"description\":\"Was the question answered successfully? Does it include enough context to write great marketing copy for the business?\"},\"reasoning\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"Explain using the criteria why the question was or was not answered successfully.\"}},\"required\":[\"success\",\"reasoning\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"tool_choice\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"name\":\"extract\"},\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"\\n        # QA Evaluation Criteria\\n\\nALL answers must meet ALL four:\\n\\n1. **Specific** - Not vague (could describe 1000 businesses = fail)\\n2. **Actionable** - Can write marketing copy directly from it\\n3. **Authentic** - Their words, not marketing jargon (\\\"leverage synergies\\\" = fail)\\n4. **Insightful** - Shows understanding of business/audience\\n\\nClose but missing one element = NOT GREAT yet. Be critical but fair.\\n\\nOutput JSON: `{ success: boolean, reasoning: string }`\\n\\n        \\n        # QA: Solution\\n\\n**Need:**\\n- Mechanism: what they actually deliver/do\\n- Transformation: before → after state\\n- Differentiator: why THIS vs alternatives\\n- Deliverable: concrete outputs, not promises\\n- Timeline: when do results happen\\n\\n**Hormozi Value Equation - Score each mentally (0-10):**\\n\\n**Dream Outcome:** Specific + quantified?\\n- Weak: \\\"more productive\\\"\\n- Strong: \\\"reclaim 10 hrs/week, finish side project\\\"\\n\\n**Perceived Likelihood:** WHY it works?\\n- Need: method/process, track record, unique approach\\n- Missing: just claiming \\\"it works\\\" with no proof\\n\\n**Time Delay:** Timeline mentioned?\\n- Good: \\\"results in 30 days\\\" or \\\"first win in 7 days\\\"\\n- Missing: no indication when transformation happens\\n\\n**Effort & Sacrifice:** Work required clear?\\n- Good: \\\"15min/day\\\" or \\\"we do it for you\\\"\\n- Missing: unclear what customer must do\\n\\n**If 3+ categories score <7 → fail**\\n\\n**Unique Mechanism (Hormozi):**\\nNamed process = strong differentiation\\n- Good: \\\"The 4-Phase Profit System\\\"\\n- Weak: \\\"our approach\\\" / \\\"our method\\\"\\n\\n**Red flags:**\\n- Feature dumps without benefits → can't write transformation copy\\n- \\\"Better/faster/cheaper\\\" → weak differentiation, need mechanism\\n- Vague \\\"I help X do Y\\\" → need concrete deliverable\\n- Unclear done-for-you vs DIY → affects value perception\\n- Copying competitor language verbatim → no differentiation\\n\\n        \\n        <current_topic>solution</current_topic>\\n        \\n        <user_answer>Friend of the Pod has over 100+ filters to find the perfect guest for your show.\\n                We use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\n                We also use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\n                But what sets us apart is that we've trained proprietary models on messages that \\n                successful podcast hosts receive. We use this data to filter out pitches that \\n                are predicted to not be a good fit for your show.\\n            </user_answer>\\n        \\n        <existing_memory>No answer yet</existing_memory>\\n        \\n        <task>\\n        Evaluate if their answer is GREAT based on the criteria above.\\n        Output JSON: { \\\"success\\\": boolean, \\\"reasoning\\\": string }\\n        </task>\\n    \"}]}"
          },
          "queryString": [],
          "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages"
        },
        "response": {
          "bodySize": 2885,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 2885,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01DwfsBg3pZ9pM4BCm5WJkn3\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01Adsw5SoFF8q728dR75L6uG\",\"name\":\"extract\",\"input\":{\"success\":false,\"reasoning\":\"The answer fails on multiple critical criteria:\\n\\n**Specific (FAIL):** \\\"100+ filters\\\" and \\\"AI matching\\\" are generic features that describe dozens of podcast platforms and guest-matching tools. No specificity about WHICH filters, HOW they work, or what makes them unique beyond \\\"we trained models.\\\"\\n\\n**Actionable (PARTIAL):** Can extract \\\"saves time finding guests\\\" but lacks concrete deliverables. Missing: How many guests per week? Time saved? Quality metrics? Can't write compelling copy without knowing the actual transformation.\\n\\n**Authentic (FAIL):** Heavy marketing jargon (\\\"proprietary models,\\\" \\\"trained on data,\\\" \\\"predicted to not be a good fit\\\") without explaining what this means in plain language. Sounds like tech speak, not founder voice. The repetition of the same sentence suggests copy-paste filler.\\n\\n**Insightful (FAIL):** No evidence of understanding the HOST's actual pain. What's the real problem? Is it:\\n- Wasting 5 hours vetting bad pitches?\\n- Missing great guests because they're buried in noise?\\n- Getting pitched irrelevant guests constantly?\\n\\nThe answer doesn't reveal which problem they solve or why it matters.\\n\\n**Hormozi Value Equation Scoring:**\\n- **Dream Outcome:** \\\"Find perfect guest\\\" is vague. What does \\\"perfect\\\" mean? (Score: 4/10)\\n- **Perceived Likelihood:** \\\"We trained models on successful pitches\\\" is a claim without proof or mechanism explanation. Why does this work? (Score: 5/10)\\n- **Time Delay:** Zero mention of timeline. How fast do results happen? (Score: 2/10)\\n- **Effort & Sacrifice:** Unclear if this is done-for-you or DIY. Do hosts still have to review filtered results? (Score: 3/10)\\n\\n**Red Flags Present:**\\n- Feature dump (\\\"100+ filters,\\\" \\\"AI matching\\\") without transformation\\n- Vague differentiation (\\\"proprietary models\\\" = black box, not compelling)\\n- No concrete deliverable (guests per week? quality score? time saved?)\\n- Repetitive sentence suggests weak positioning\\n- \\\"Perfect guest\\\" is subjective—needs definition\\n\\n**What's Missing for GREAT:**\\n- Specific transformation: \\\"Reduce guest vetting time from 4 hours to 30 minutes per episode\\\"\\n- Named mechanism: \\\"The [X] Matching System\\\"\\n- Proof: \\\"Hosts using our filters report 3x higher episode performance\\\"\\n- Timeline: \\\"First qualified guest in 48 hours\\\"\\n- Clarity: \\\"We do the filtering; you just approve\\\"\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1444,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":636,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
          },
