            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"extract\",\"description\":\"A function available to call.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"success\":{\"type\":\"boolean\",\"description\":\"Was the question answered successfully? Does it include enough context to write great marketing copy for the business?\"},\"reasoning\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"Explain using the criteria why the question was or was not answered successfully.\"}},\"required\":[\"success\",\"reasoning\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"tool_choice\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"name\":\"extract\"},\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"\\n        # QA Evaluation Criteria\\n\\nALL answers must meet ALL four:\\n\\n1. **Specific** - Not vague (could describe 1000 businesses = fail)\\n2. **Actionable** - Can write marketing copy directly from it\\n3. **Authentic** - Their words, not marketing jargon (\\\"leverage synergies\\\" = fail)\\n4. **Insightful** - Shows understanding of business/audience\\n\\nClose but missing one element = NOT GREAT yet. Be critical but fair.\\n\\nOutput JSON: `{ success: boolean, reasoning: string }`\\n\\n        \\n        # QA: Solution\\n\\n**Need:**\\n\\n- What they deliver (mechanism/service/product)\\n- The transformation (what changes for customer)\\n- Why it's different (some differentiator)\\n\\n**Hormozi Value Equation - Use as guidance, not strict scoring:**\\n\\n**Dream Outcome:**\\nDo they articulate WHAT the customer will achieve?\\n\\n- Weak: totally vague \\\"you'll do better\\\"\\n- OK: \\\"you'll be more organized\\\"\\n- Strong: \\\"reclaim 10 hrs/week, finish side project\\\"\\n\\n**Perceived Likelihood:**\\nIs there ANY reason to believe it works?\\n\\n- Weak: just claims with nothing\\n- OK: mentions their experience/process\\n- Strong: named process, track record, proof\\n\\n**Time Delay:**\\nDo they mention timeline at all?\\n\\n- Weak: no timeline mentioned\\n- OK: vague timeframe \\\"within months\\\"\\n- Strong: \\\"first win in 7 days, full results in 90\\\"\\n\\n**Effort & Sacrifice:**\\nIs it clear what customer must do?\\n\\n- Weak: completely unclear\\n- OK: some indication of involvement\\n- Strong: \\\"15min/day\\\" or \\\"we do it for you\\\"\\n\\n**Evaluation approach:**\\n\\n- If answer explains what they do + some outcome + some differentiator → likely PASS\\n- Don't require perfect Hormozi offer - that's advanced\\n- Named mechanism is NICE but not required\\n- Focus: Can we write compelling copy from this?\\n\\n**Red flags that DO fail:**\\n\\n- Pure feature list with zero benefits\\n- \\\"I help people\\\" with no explanation\\n- Completely generic \\\"we're better/faster/cheaper\\\" with nothing specific\\n- Copying competitor language word-for-word\\n- No mention of deliverable or outcome whatsoever\\n\\n**Remember:**\\nWe're building landing pages, not $100M offers. Good enough > perfect.\\nIf they explain WHAT they do, WHO benefits, and WHY choose them → probably pass.\\n\\n        \\n        <current_topic>solution</current_topic>\\n        \\n        <user_answer>Hosts book guests that are proven to drive 15-20% higher engagement</user_answer>\\n        \\n        <existing_memory>No answer yet</existing_memory>\\n        \\n        <task>\\n        Evaluate if their answer is GREAT based on the criteria above.\\n        Output JSON: { \\\"success\\\": boolean, \\\"reasoning\\\": string }\\n        </task>\\n    \"}]}"
