          "postData": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"extract\",\"description\":\"A function available to call.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"success\":{\"type\":\"boolean\",\"description\":\"Was the question answered successfully? Does it include enough context to write great marketing copy for the business?\"},\"reasoning\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"Explain using the criteria why the question was or was not answered successfully.\"}},\"required\":[\"success\",\"reasoning\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"tool_choice\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"name\":\"extract\"},\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"\\n        # QA Evaluation Criteria\\n\\nALL answers must meet ALL four:\\n\\n1. **Specific** - Not vague (could describe 1000 businesses = fail)\\n2. **Actionable** - Can write marketing copy directly from it\\n3. **Authentic** - Their words, not marketing jargon (\\\"leverage synergies\\\" = fail)\\n4. **Insightful** - Shows understanding of business/audience\\n\\nClose but missing one element = NOT GREAT yet. Be critical but fair.\\n\\nOutput JSON: `{ success: boolean, reasoning: string }`\\n\\n        \\n        # QA: Solution\\n\\n**Core question: Can we write compelling landing page copy from this?**\\n\\n**Minimum needed:**\\n\\n- What they deliver (the thing customer gets)\\n- Some indication of outcome/benefit (even implied)\\n- Something that differentiates them (doesn't have to be huge)\\n\\n**Look for:**\\n\\n- Describes the actual product/service\\n- Mentions what problem it solves OR result it creates\\n- Has SOME hook that's not purely generic\\n\\n**Hormozi Value Equation - Use as inspiration, not requirements:**\\n\\nIf they mention ANY of these, note it positively:\\n\\n- Specific outcome (quantified or clear transformation)\\n- Why it works (mechanism, process, expertise)\\n- Timeline (how fast)\\n- Effort level (how easy)\\n\\nBut they don't need ALL of these. Even 1-2 is often enough for a landing page.\\n\\n**Unique Mechanism bonus:**\\nIf they have a named process or proprietary approach, that's GREAT.\\nBut it's not required. Many good solutions don't have fancy names.\\n\\n**What DOES fail:**\\n\\n- Can't explain what they actually do\\n- Zero indication of benefit or outcome\\n- Nothing differentiating at all (could be anyone)\\n- Pure jargon with no substance\\n- \\\"We're like [competitor] but better\\\" with no specifics\\n\\n**Examples that PASS:**\\n\\n\\\"I create Instagram content for local restaurants. I come on-site monthly, shoot 30 days of content in 3 hours, and handle all editing and scheduling. Restaurants see 40% higher engagement.\\\"\\n→ Has mechanism, outcome, timeline, differentiation. PASS.\\n\\n\\\"I help e-commerce brands with email marketing using my proprietary AI that analyzes which products to promote when. Built on data from 500+ stores.\\\"\\n→ Has unique mechanism, clear service, proof/credibility. PASS.\\n\\n\\\"We use AI-powered filtering with 100+ filters to match podcast hosts with perfect guests. What sets us apart: we trained models on successful pitches from top shows.\\\"\\n→ Has mechanism, clear value prop, strong differentiator. PASS.\\n\\n**Examples that FAIL:**\\n\\n\\\"I help businesses grow using innovative strategies.\\\"\\n→ No mechanism, no specifics, pure generic. FAIL.\\n\\n\\\"We provide consulting services.\\\"\\n→ What kind? For whom? Doing what? FAIL.\\n\\n**Remember:**\\nLanding pages need enough to be compelling, not perfect.\\nIf you can picture writing \\\"Here's how it works...\\\" and \\\"Why choose us...\\\" sections, it passes.\\n\\n        \\n        <current_topic>solution</current_topic>\\n        \\n        <user_answer>Friend of the Pod has over 100+ filters to find the perfect guest for your show.\\n                We use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\n                We also use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\n                But what sets us apart is that we've trained proprietary models on messages that \\n                successful podcast hosts receive. We use this data to filter out pitches that \\n                are predicted to not be a good fit for your show.\\n            </user_answer>\\n        \\n        <existing_memory>No answer yet</existing_memory>\\n        \\n        <task>\\n        Evaluate if their answer is GREAT based on the criteria above.\\n        Output JSON: { \\\"success\\\": boolean, \\\"reasoning\\\": string }\\n        </task>\\n    \"}]}"
          },
          "queryString": [],
          "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages"
        },
        "response": {
          "bodySize": 2040,
