            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"extract\",\"description\":\"A function available to call.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"success\":{\"type\":\"boolean\",\"description\":\"Was the question answered successfully? Does it include enough context to write great marketing copy for the business?\"},\"reasoning\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"Explain using the criteria why the question was or was not answered successfully.\"}},\"required\":[\"success\",\"reasoning\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"tool_choice\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"name\":\"extract\"},\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"\\n        # QA Evaluation Criteria\\n\\nALL answers must meet ALL four:\\n\\n1. **Specific** - Not vague (could describe 1000 businesses = fail)\\n2. **Actionable** - Can write marketing copy directly from it\\n3. **Authentic** - Their words, not marketing jargon (\\\"leverage synergies\\\" = fail)\\n4. **Insightful** - Shows understanding of business/audience\\n\\nClose but missing one element = NOT GREAT yet. Be critical but fair.\\n\\nOutput JSON: `{ success: boolean, reasoning: string }`\\n\\n        \\n        # QA: Social Proof\\n\\n**Social proof is broader than testimonials**: founder story, background, personal results, research, community size all count.\\n\\n**For early-stage (no testimonials)**: Founder credibility, personal transformation, process credibility, relatability = valid proof\\n\\n**High-impact proof** (Hormozi):\\n- Quantified results: \\\"Average client adds $50K\\\"\\n- Specific case studies with numbers\\n- Volume: \\\"500+ businesses\\\"\\n- Authority: \\\"Featured in Forbes\\\"\\n\\n**Reject**:\\n- \\\"I don't have testimonials\\\" without offering alternatives\\n- Generic praise without specifics (\\\"clients love me\\\")\\n- Vague credentials (\\\"10 years experience\\\" without context)\\n\\n**Privacy/NDA** → industry descriptors OK (\\\"Fortune 500 SaaS\\\")\\n\\n        \\n        <current_topic>socialProof</current_topic>\\n        \\n        <user_answer>Over 10k creators use Friend of the Pod to find guests for their shows.\\n    Real case: Host found 3 guests in 10 minutes instead of 5 hours of manual outreach, leading to 2 viral episodes</user_answer>\\n        \\n        <existing_memory>No answer yet</existing_memory>\\n        \\n        <task>\\n        Evaluate if their answer is GREAT based on the criteria above.\\n        Output JSON: { \\\"success\\\": boolean, \\\"reasoning\\\": string }\\n        </task>\\n    \"}]}"
          },
          "queryString": [],
          "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages"
        },
        "response": {
          "bodySize": 1880,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1880,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01QeKERkQX2kpWYHA8P17SDw\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01PZKn933whWYXuQJECZGBqj\",\"name\":\"extract\",\"input\":{\"success\":true,\"reasoning\":\"This answer meets all four criteria:\\n\\n1. **Specific** - Not vague. Clearly identifies the product (Friend of the Pod), the user base (creators), and a concrete use case (finding podcast guests). The case study includes specific numbers: 3 guests in 10 minutes vs 5 hours, and a measurable outcome (2 viral episodes).\\n\\n2. **Actionable** - Marketing copy writes itself: \\\"Save 4 hours 50 minutes per guest search\\\" or \\\"Find 3 qualified guests in 10 minutes instead of 5 hours of outreach.\\\" The time-saving benefit is immediately clear and compelling.\\n\\n3. **Authentic** - Uses real language and metrics without marketing jargon. \\\"Found 3 guests in 10 minutes\\\" is how a real user would describe it. No \\\"leverage,\\\" \\\"synergies,\\\" or corporate speak. The \\\"2 viral episodes\\\" outcome feels like genuine business impact, not manufactured praise.\\n\\n4. **Insightful** - Demonstrates understanding of the creator's pain point (manual outreach is time-consuming) and shows the direct business impact (viral episodes = audience growth/success). The volume proof (10k+ creators) establishes scale without being the only proof point.\\n\\nThe answer combines high-impact proof elements: quantified results (time saved, guest count), a specific case study with numbers, volume (10k+ users), and a tangible outcome (viral episodes). This is exactly the type of social proof that converts.\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1192,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":376,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
